ezing profit margins. Companies are attempting price hikes, but oversupply makes it difficult to pass on the full cost burden. Analysts suggest that improved demand and capacity utilization are key for future price stability.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/cement-industry-faces-cost-shock-as-west-asia-conflict-drives-up-prices/129897264?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-262940/129897264.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}]}